Cases 14TR4785, 14TR4781, 14TR47841, 14TR4783, 14CM1423, 14TR4782, 15CM1031, and 15CM404.  Defendant Lino Cortez in court with attorney John Paul Marchan.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Patrick Ryan appeared as interpreter, sworn in.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count # 2 is dismissed and read in.  State gives recommendations.  Attorney Marchan makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following to count #1:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of 
80 days Huber consecutive to 15CM1031 with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 0 days).  

Term of Probation: 18 months
Conditions of Probation:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
No contact with Victim Jose Arias or his residence
Condition Time: 30 days in the Waukesha County Jail Stayed
COSTS:  $243.00.  Bail to be applied.  Remainder of bail to be applied to case # 14TR4781.
